WorkItem.Description:
Hi,

I am manipulating tables in a Word document. 
I have a simple test code which checks whether a table cell is odd or even, and sets it to bold if it's odd.

If I try to assign a boolean value, the compiler gives me a 'cannot convert bool to int'error. 
If I try to assign an integer value, the code compiles but raises an exception. 

//bc is boolean and initialized to true.
//dbg() is a helper function and works.
//tcel is word table's cell and works. getting the value and getting a ToString() gives me 0 or -1.

if(bc == true){
    //dbg("tcel.Range.Font.Bold == " + tcel.Range.Font.Bold.ToString());
    tcel.Range.Font.Bold = -1;
}else{
    //dbg("tcel.Range.Font.Bold == " + tcel.Range.Font.Bold.ToString());
    tcel.Range.Font.Bold = 0;
}

